meanings.definition: Not complete; lacking some part or element.
meanings.sent1: The puzzle was incomplete without the last piece.
meanings.sent2: Her homework was incomplete because she forgot to do the last question.
meanings.sent3: The cake looked incomplete without the frosting on top.
meanings.sent4: His collection of stamps felt incomplete without the rare one he was missing.
meanings.sent5: The garden seemed incomplete without the colorful flowers blooming.

meanings.definition: Not fully formed or developed; unfinished.
meanings.sent1: The artist's painting remained incomplete until she added the final touches.
meanings.sent2: The story was incomplete as the last chapter was missing.
meanings.sent3: The joke felt incomplete without the punchline.
meanings.sent4: His plan to redecorate the room was incomplete without new curtains.
meanings.sent5: The song sounded incomplete without the chorus at the end.
